HEADWORD: Barrenness
<hw>Bar"ren*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The condition of being barren;
sterility; unproductiveness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A total <qex>barrenness</qex> of invention.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

